  <H1>HIPR2 - Acquisition</H1>
</CENTER>
<P>
<h4>The acquisition of HIPR2 is a little confusing. In one web page it is posted 
  as a free web resource, while elsewhere listed as unavailable at the moment 
  (with the installation instructions)! </H4>
<h4><i> &quot;No part of the material may be reproduced or transmitted in any 
  form or by any means, or stored in a computer for retrieval purposes or otherwise, 
  without written permission from the authors&quot;</i> <a href="http://www.dai.ed.ac.uk/HIPR2/copyrght.htm">(HIPRpage1)</a></H4>
<h4> <i>&quot;HIPR2 is not for sale at present and is made available to the world 
  for free over the WWW&quot;</i> <a href="http://www.dai.ed.ac.uk/HIPR2/sales.htm">(HIPRpage2)</a> 
</H4>
<p></p>
